				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming<a name="6917"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 1 03 11:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a question about Swarm kiting that has been bothering me for a while.  I understand the basic concept:
<br />

<br />
1.  pull group of mobs
<br />
2.  charm one in group
<br />
3.  Have new pet attack one of the others in swarm
<br />
4.  Watch pet health.  When low, break charm and kill pet.
<br />
5.  Repeat steps 2 - 4 until no mobs left.
<br />

<br />
My problem/question is centered around item #4.  When you release your pet, you are, essentially, in a situation where you have multiple NPCs beating down another NPC.  Isn't it the case that if an NPC gets the killing blow on another NPC that you are fighting, you DON'T get the xp for that kill?  Isn't that the basis of guards &quot;kill stealing&quot; in newbie areas?  If that is true, it seems to me like the other mobs would get the killing blow more often than not, leaving you with very little XP gain.
<br />

<br />
So, my real question is how does this differ from the case of a guard walking up to you and getting the last blow on that diseased rat you were killing? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
