			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming<a name="7147"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 9 03 2:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are a couple options for retargeting pet and target.
<br />

<br />
My method....  My pet is practically always targetted with this method.  I have 2 hotkeys
<br />

<br />
[Pet Attack Hotkey]
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
/pet report health
<br />
/pet target
<br />

<br />
[Report Health Hotkey]
<br />
/pet report health
<br />
/pet target
<br />

<br />
By adding the /pet target line to both buttons, as soon as I send him in to attack I have retargeted him.  If for any reason I need to untarget him, a report health has him back.
<br />

<br />
So initial engagement is:
<br />
Target pet-to-be and charm (pet is targeted)
<br />
Target prey (prey is targeted)
<br />
esc-tab-tab to store prey in tab buffer (nothing-me-prey targeted in rapid order)
<br />
Pet Attack Hotkey (pet engaged with prey and pet targeted)
<br />
Report Health Hotkey frequently to update pet health
<br />

<br />

<br />
The other option:
<br />
You can set your tab buffer functioanlity to toggle between your last 2 targets (leaving you out of the mix).  Then just tab between them.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
